        "***R-squared ***(\\(R^{2}\\)),\n",
        " also known as the Coefficient of Determination, is a statistical metric used to evaluate the performance of a regression model.It measures how well your model's predictions match the actual data points by calculating the proportion of variance in the target variable (\\(y\\)) that can be explained by your input features (\\(X\\)).\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        " Formula=1-(SSR)/(SST)\n",
        "\n",
        " (Residual Sum of Squares): The sum of the squared differences between the actual values\n",
        " and your model's predicted values\n",
        " . This represents the error your model made.\n",
        "\n",
        " (Total Sum of Squares): The sum of the squared differences between the actual values and the average value. This represents the total variance present in the data before any model is applied"
